Text:
Citi announced third quarter 2022 results today. 
 
For complete information, please visit our Investor Relations website: https://t.co/m28s8r5L2A https://t.co/4jmPbXhkEx

‚ÄúWe continue to shrink our operations in and exposure to Russia. To be clear, our intention is to wind down our presence in that country.‚Äù ‚Äì Jane Fraser, CEO   
 
More info: https://t.co/eR5cXeqTMZ

‚ÄúIn terms of simplification, we continue to make progress on the divestitures of our international consumer businesses and the elimination of their associated stranded costs.‚Äù ‚Äì Jane Fraser, CEO
 
More information: https://t.co/eR5cXeqTMZ

‚ÄúI am generally pleased with the advances we are making in the key drivers of the strategy we laid out for you in March.‚Äù ‚Äì Jane Fraser, CEO
 
More info: https://t.co/eR5cXeqTMZ

‚ÄúU.S. Personal Banking further solidified its growth trajectory. Cards sales, ANR, interest earning balances and customer acquisition all saw good growth, and we continued to increase digital uptake.‚Äù ‚Äì Jane Fraser, CEO
 
More information: https://t.co/eR5cXe9QKZ

‚ÄúIn Fixed Income, we matched last year‚Äôs particularly good showing through our longstanding strength in FX.‚Äù ‚Äì Jane Fraser, CEO
 
More info: https://t.co/eR5cXeqTMZ

‚ÄúSecurities Services was up 15%, despite assets under custody being impacted by the declines in equity markets.‚Äù ‚Äì Jane Fraser, CEO
 
More info: https://t.co/eR5cXe9QKZ

‚ÄúServices delivered another very strong quarter. TTS saw revenues up 40% year-over-year, with growth in each business and in fees.‚Äù ‚Äì Jane Fraser, CEO
 
More information: https://t.co/eR5cXeqTMZ

‚ÄúThe U.S. economy, however, remains relatively resilient. So while we are seeing signs of economic slowing, consumers and corporates remain healthy.‚Äù -Jane Fraser, CEO
 
More information: https://t.co/eR5cXeqTMZ

‚ÄúIn the Eurozone and the U.K. the supply shocks are most severe, growth prospects have deteriorated sharply, and headline inflation is running at nearly 10%.‚Äù ‚Äì Jane Fraser, CEO
 
More information: https://t.co/eR5cXe9QKZ

‚ÄúThere is accumulating evidence of slowing global growth and we now expect to experience rolling country level recessions, starting this quarter.‚Äù ‚Äì Jane Fraser, CEO
 
More information: https://t.co/eR5cXeqTMZ

‚ÄúWe are certainly still living through interesting times and overall I am pleased with how our bank is navigating through them.‚Äù ‚Äì Jane Fraser, CEO

More information: https://t.co/eR5cXeqTMZ

Text:
Citi announced second quarter 2022 results today. 
 
For complete information, please visit our Investor Relations website: https://t.co/RfuVCWj2qI https://t.co/RWcS8iA5nX

‚ÄúOur team delivered solid results and the bank is in a very strong position to weather uncertain times while playing to our strengths. I am confident about the path ahead and pleased with our early progress.‚Äù ‚Äî CEO Jane Fraser. More info: https://t.co/eR5cXeqTMZ
‚ÄúIn terms of Russia, we continue to shrink the size of our business and take steps to reduce our financial exposure.‚Äù ‚Äî CEO Jane Fraser. More information: https://t.co/eR5cXeqTMZ

‚ÄúWhile the world has changed since we presented our Investor Day to you in March, our strategy has not. We have continued to execute it with discipline and urgency.‚Äù  ‚Äî CEO Jane Fraser. More information: https://t.co/eR5cXeqTMZ

‚ÄúThe market volatility that we saw in the first quarter continued into the second, driving corporate clients in particular to be more active in risk management, contributing to revenue growth of 25% in Markets.‚Äù ‚Äî CEO Jane Fraser. More info: https://t.co/eR5cXeqTMZ
‚ÄúServices continued to show excellent momentum, with revenues up 28% year-over-year.‚Äù ‚Äî CEO Jane Fraser. More information: https://t.co/eR5cXeqTMZ

Citi CEO Jane Fraser discusses second quarter 2022 financial results. 
                                                                                                        
Read the full report here: https://t.co/xUgkLS7x8s https://t.co/AMkhve22aB

‚ÄúA rebound in China also faces constraints given the potential for future lockdowns, amount of leverage in the Chinese economy and stress in their property sector.‚Äù ‚Äî CEO Jane Fraser. More information: https://t.co/eR5cXeqTMZ

‚ÄúI am just back from Europe, which is a different story. We expect a very difficult winter is coming due to disruptions in the energy supply.‚Äù ‚Äî CEO Jane Fraser. More information: https://t.co/eR5cXeqTMZ
‚ÄúThat said, while sentiment has shifted, little of the data I see tells me the U.S. is on the cusp of a recession.‚Äù ‚Äî CEO Jane Fraser. More information: https://t.co/eR5cXeqTMZ

‚ÄúThere are mounting costs to the series of supply shocks we have experienced. And now we need to pay attention to an additional ‚ÄòS‚Äô in ESG and that is Security.‚Äù ‚Äî CEO Jane Fraser. More information: https://t.co/eR5cXeqTMZ

‚ÄúWhen we last spoke, we said the macro and geopolitical outlook was complex and uncertain. So, in one sense, little has changed. However, the headwinds have certainly crystalized.‚Äù ‚Äî CEO Jane Fraser. More information: https://t.co/eR5cXeqTMZ
